definitions.definition: To travel from one end of something to the other.
definitions.example: The train went through the tunnel.

definitions.definition: To examine or scrutinize (a number or series of things).
definitions.example: Every morning, she went through her mail over a cup of coffee.

definitions.definition: To enact or recite the entire length of (something).

definitions.example: I went through a lengthy immigration process before I was allowed across the border.

definitions.definition: To use up or wear out (clothing etc.).
definitions.example: Her family drinks so much milk that they go through two gallons a week.

definitions.definition: To progress to the next stage of something.
definitions.example: If United don't lose by more than 2 goals, they should go through to the next round.

definitions.definition: To reach an intended destination after passing through some process.
definitions.example: I don't think my instant messages are going through.
